=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides a summary of a task related to creating an engagement from an
opportunity. This structure contains key information about the task's
status, associated identifiers, and any failure details.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 EngagementId => Str

The unique identifier of the engagement created as a result of the
task. This field is populated when the task is completed successfully.


=head2 EngagementInvitationId => Str

The unique identifier of the Engagement Invitation.


=head2 Message => Str

A detailed message providing additional information about the task,
especially useful in case of failures. This field may contain error
details or other relevant information about the task's execution


=head2 OpportunityId => Str

The unique identifier of the original Opportunity from which the
Engagement is being created. This field helps track the source of the
Engagement creation task.


=head2 ReasonCode => Str

A code indicating the specific reason for a task failure. This field is
populated when the task status is FAILED and provides a categorized
reason for the failure.


=head2 ResourceSnapshotJobId => Str

The identifier of the resource snapshot job associated with this task,
if a snapshot was created as part of the Engagement creation process.


=head2 StartTime => Str

The timestamp indicating when the task was initiated, in RFC 3339 5.6
date-time format.


=head2 TaskArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) uniquely identifying this task within
AWS. This ARN can be used for referencing the task in other AWS
services or APIs.


=head2 TaskId => Str

A unique identifier for a specific task.


=head2 TaskStatus => Str

The current status of the task.



